The CVData.mdf File

The CVData.mdf file stores all primary data for CABINET VISION and the S2M CENTER.

The following is the breakdown of the tables and their fields:

Assembly

This table stores Catalog Objects.

Field

Description

ID

A unique number to identify the record

AssemblyCatalogID

A cross reference to [AssemblyCatalog].[ID]

Name

The name of the assembly.

Description

A description for the assembly.

ParentID

A reference number to the parent assembly if this object is part of a group

AliasOf

A reference number to the main assembly if this object has been cloned. Zero, if the object is a main assembly.

Height

The default height of the object. If the object is saved with the Preserve Size option selected it will come out of the library to the saved size. Otherwise, it will revert to the default height for this object type.

Width

The default width of the object.

Depth

The default depth of the object. If the object is saved with the Preserve Size option selected it will come out of the library to the saved size. Otherwise, it will revert to the default depth for this object type.

AssemblyClassTypeID

A cross reference to [refAssemblyClassType].[ID]

AssemblyUnitTypeID

A cross reference to [refAssemblyUnitType].[ID]

HingeLeft

A Boolean flag set true if assembly is hinged on the left/top

HingeRight

A Boolean flag set true if assembly is hinged on the right/bottom

AutoFill

A Boolean flag if set to true will use this object for automatically filling empty spaces on the wall with objects.

Weight

The weight of the object in kilograms - Used in many stock catalogs for pricing.

Cubes

The mass of the object in cubic meters - Used in many stock catalogs for pricing.

Accessory

A Boolean flag if set to true indicates this assembly has additional information in the Accessory table.

Price

A flat cost that is to be associated with the item.

HingeChar

Index into Name indicating what character represent the hinge direction

Tags

A list of text strings used to search and categorize the assembly

AssemblyShapeID

A cross reference to the [AssemblyShape].[ID] field.

rGUID

Unique record identifier

LastUpdate

Time stamp on when this record was last modified

ContributorID

A cross reference to [Contributor].[ID] indicating the source of this item

AssemblyCatalog

Field

Description

ID

A unique number to reference the assembly catalog

ContributorID

A cross reference to [Contributor].[ID] indicating the source of the assembly catalog

Name

The name for this assembly catalog

Description

The description of this assembly catalog

Ordinal

The order in which the catalog will appear in the list

MigrationData

The original imported data

ModularIncrement

During Auto-Fill objects placed will seek the same size while holding the differences to less than this value

Data

Additional XML data

Lic

Internal data

rGUID

Unique record identifier

LastUpdate

Time stamp on when this record was last modified

Field

Description

ID

A unique number to identify the record

A cross reference to [AssemblyCatalog].[ID]

Name

The door style's name.

Description

The door style's description.

Ordinal

The order in which the style is to be displayed

AssemblyCatalogPriceLabelID

A cross-reference to the [AssemblyCatalogPriceLabel].[ID] field. When this Door Style is selected, it will use the prices associated with this price label.

ContributorID

A cross reference to [Contributor].[ID] indicating the source of this item

LastUpdate

Time stamp on when this record was last modified

Description

A unique number to identify the record

AssemblyDoorStyleTypeID

A cross-reference to the [refAssemblyDoorStyleType].[ID] field.

DoorID

A cross-reference to the [Door].[ID] field.

Selected

When multiple doors of a type are available for a style - this indicates the default ID.

UpCharge

An upcharge amount associated with this door style.

UpChargeIncludeDoorCost

A Boolean value set true to include the door catalog price in the upcharge value

UpChargePercent

An upcharge percent associated with door style.

MaxDrawerHeight

For drawer fronts only.  Indicates the maximum height this style should be used for a drawer front.

AssemblyCatalogExtraModularInfo

Field

Description

ID

A unique number to identify the record

AssemblyCatalogID

Cross reference to [AssemblyCatalog].[ID]

BaseHeight

The default height for a base assembly.

BaseDepth

The default depth for a base assembly.

UpperHeight

The default height for an upper assembly.

UpperDepth

The default depth for a upper assembly.

The default height for an tall assembly.

TallDepth

The default depth for a tall assembly.

TwoPullWidth

The horizontal width of a drawer before the drawer receives two pulls.

rGUID

Unique record identifier

AssemblyCatalogLinePricing

Field

Description

ID

A unique number to identify the record

AssemblyCatalogID

A cross reference to [AssemblyCatalog].[ID]

Ordinal

The order in which the record will appear and be evaluated in the stock pricing table

Formula

The pricing equation for this line item.  Equation can consist of raw numbers, job totals, variables, previous line numbers and options

Reference

A short unique string to identify the purpose of the record

Description

A description of the record

System

A Boolean flag indicating that the record was created by the system.  These formulas can not be modified by either the manufacturer of the dealer

Locked

A Boolean flag indicating that the record was created by the manufacturer.  These items can only be modified from the catalog editor

ShowAtTotal

A Boolean flag indicating if this record Reference and Result of Formula should appear in the bid center as a price total.  Here the manufacturer or the dealer can decide what data is displayed

PerJob

A Boolean flag indicating in the record should be evaluated for each cabinet or only once per job.  As an example If you had a 20 cabinet job and the formula was simply 100 and PerJob = $100 -- Not PerJob = $2,000 ($100 x 20 cabinets)

ShowAtCabinet

A Boolean flag indicating if this record should appear for an individual cabinet breakout in the bid center.

ShowAtAcc

A Boolean flag indicating if this record should appear for an individual accessory breakout in the bid center.

ContributorID

A cross reference to [Contributor].[ID] indicating the source of this item

LastUpdate

Time stamp on when this record was last modified

AssemblyExtraAccessoryInfo

Field

Description

ID

A unique number to identify the record

AssemblyID

A cross reference to [Assembly].[ID]

Graphic

A boolean value set to true if the accessory is visible, false if the accessory serves as an up charge.

ColumnPricing

A boolean value set to true if the accessory has multiple price options.

UpCharge

A flat cost associated with the accessory.

UpChargePercent

The up charge percent this accessory is to add to a Cabinet or Job.

Children

A boolean value set to true if the accessory has children, set false if the accessory is only one part.

AssemblyExtraInfo

Field

Description

ID

A unique number to identify the record

AssemblyID

A cross reference to [Assembly].[ID]

Signature

An identifier used to cross reference prices from other stock catalogs for similar cabinets. The signature is comprised of the cabinet type, end types, and sectioning information.

DXF=0x8000

PresConst=x200k

NoDim=x800k

Att=x1000k,Note=x2000k

CAD=x4000k

Height=x10000k

Depth=x20000k

SwitchSize=x40000k

Finish=x80000k

StretchWidth

A boolean flag set true if assembly can be resized in width

StretchHeight

A boolean flag set true if assembly can be resized in height

StretchDepth

A boolean flag set true if assembly can be resized in depth

AssemblyElevationTypeID

A cross reference to [refAssemblyElevationType].[ID]

SnapToWall

A boolean flag set true if assembly snaps to wall when placed

SnapToCorner

A boolean flag set true if assembly snaps to corner when placed

ExtraBaseDoors

Used exclusively for stock catalog pricing. The number of additional doors to add to a cabinet. The doors are not visible, this field is utilized for stock catalogs that setup false door/drawer counts for their pricing structure.

ExtraUpperDoors

See ExtraBaseDoors.

ExtraDrawers

See ExtraBaseDoors.

A value representing the Length displayed in output increment and precision.

A value representing the Width of the Part without banding or EDX value.

A value representing the Length of the Part without banding or EDY value.

The user comment for the Part.

The primary Part edge that rests against the point-to-point pins:

1 = Left

2 = Top

3 = Right

4 = Bottom

Mirror

A Boolean value set to true if the Part is output to a mirrored zone.

Shaped

A Boolean value set to true if the Part is shaped.

Outline

 

 

 

 

 

 

Shape in an ASCII comma delimited string.

Format:

(node count,x1,x2 ,radius1,flags1,.....xN,yN, radiusN,flagsN)

Flags:

0x08 = VTX_Radius

0x0400 = VTX_ArcLine

0x010000 = VTX_Visible

OutlineToolID

Reference to [Tool].[ID] linking a Tool to use for the outline of this Part.

GangBore

A Boolean value set to true if the Part has gang boring.

HorizontalBore

A Boolean value set to true if the Part has horizontal boring.

Reference to [Machine].[ID] linking this Part to the preferred Machine to use for primary output.

PrefSecMachineID

Reference to [Machine].[ID] linking this Part to the preferred Machine to use for secondary output.

Margin

Margin around part for Nesting.

HasBanding

A Boolean value set to true if the Edge Banding table contains data for this Part.

Banding

 

 

 

 

A Four character banding code: (Width1, Length1, Width2, Length2)

0 = None

1 = Door edging

2 = Exterior banding

3 = Interior banding

BandingCode

 

 

 

Banding code format.

Edge types; (L)ength, (W)idth, (R)adius and (A)ngle

Banding types: e(X)terior and (I)nterior

Example:1L15I1R6X1A12X - 1 Length 15" long with Interior, 1 6" Radius with eXterior, 1 Angled edge 12" long with eXterior

BandingFlags

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

CABINET VISION edge banding flags from a Parts origin related to Part Edge as follows:

(edges code_1....code_n)

Example: 6NNENEN 6 sided part from face clockwise stroke:

N = None

I = Interior

E = Exterior

D = Door

Also the User Definable Edge Characters.

FinishFace

Faces finish ID from the Material database.

FinishBack

Backs finish ID from the Material database.

FinishEdge

Edges finish ID from the Material database.

MetaFile

Binary metafile of part

Time stamp on when this record was last modified

Description

A value representing the Level at which Safe Rapid moves can take place.

A value representing the Level at which Rapid Moves can take place. This value must be less than the value set for [SafeRapidZ].

GangDrillHeadID

Cross-reference to [GangDrillHeads].[ID] linking the Gang Drill (Multi-Drill) Head.

GangFeedRate

A value representing the Feed Rate for Gang Drill (Multi-Drill) Boring.

GangSpindleSpeed

A value representing the Spindle Speed (RPMs) for the Gang Drill (Multi-Drill) Tools.

PartLeadType

 

 

 

 

 

A value representing the Normal Lead Type for the Machine:

0 = Tool Plunges

1 = Tool Ramps In

2 = Tool Ramps in leaving a Tab

3 = Onion Skin - Tool Ramps in leaving an Onion Skin

4 = Return Onion Skin - Tool ramps in leaving an Onion Skin until all Parts have been Outlined and then returns to remove Onion Skins.

SmallPartLeadType

See [PartLeadType].

VerySmallPartLeadType

See [PartLeadType].

ApplyCompOnRapid

A Boolean value set to true if the Tool Compensation is applied during the Machines Rapid Move.

RollAroundCorners

A Boolean value set to true if the Tool Path should have a Roll Radius Corner rather than an L Corner.

DrillTraverseAtSafeRapid

A Boolean value set to true if the Gang Drill (Multi-Drill) Head should move to the Safe Rapid Level between plunges.

CompensationType

 

 

 

A value representing the Compensation Type for the Machine:

0 = None  The path is Offset to Centerline.

1 = Machine  The Path is Offset to Centerline. Set the Compensation Value in the Machine Control equal to the original Tool Radius minus the Wear Radius.

2 = Tool Radius  The Path represents the outside of the Part. Set the Compensation Value in Machine Control equal to actual Tool Radius.

SaveDrawingFile

A Boolean value set to true if you want the System to Save an AlphaCAM drawing file while processing.

FileExtension

The File extension for Post output.

MaterialLengthIsX

A Boolean value set to true if the X axis on the Machine is along the Length of the Sheet.

MicAtSpoilBoard

A Boolean value set to true if Z = 0 at the Spoil Board instead of the top of the Material.
   

PointOfOrigin

 

 

 

 

A value representing the 0,0 Point (Reference/Origin) of the Machine:

0 = Bottom Left

1 = Top Left

2 = Top Right

3 = Bottom Right

XPosFromPO

A Boolean value set to true if the X axis is a positive measurement from the Machines Origin.

YPosFromPO

A Boolean value set to true if the Y axis is positive measurement from the Machines Origin.

NestCorner

 

 

 

 

A value representing the Corner the Nest (Pack) should originate from:

0 = Bottom Left

1 = Top Left

2 = Top Right

3 = Bottom Right

XYLimits

A Boolean value set to true if the Machine has X/Y Gang Drill (Multi-Drill) Head limitations.

MinX

A value representing the Minimum allowable X position for the Primary Drill on the Gang Drill (Multi-Drill) Head.

MaxX

A value representing the Maximum allowable X position for the Primary Drill on the Gang Drill (Multi-Drill) Head.

MinY

A value representing the Minimum allowable Y position for the Primary Drill on the Gang Drill (Multi-Drill) Head.

MaxY

A value representing the Maximum allowable Y position for the Primary Drill on the Gang Drill (Multi-Drill) Head.

LimitTo3Axis

A Boolean value set to true if the Machine is Limited to output Operations that occur on a cardinal work plane.

ApproachOffset

A value representing the Distance to Offset the Tool from the finished path when Ramping in and out of the Material.

OffsetFromMatBottom

Maintain the approach offset to the bottom of the material to ensure a clean edge on back of the sheet

AdjustOpenToolPathForClimbCut

A boolean value when set true will possibly reverse the direction and tool side for an open path to account for climb vs conventional cut as if the path was drawn in a CCW direction.  If false the original path direction will kept

AddFinishPassToPocket

If operation and tool are not centerline create an additional compensated path for the pocket

CenterlineInteriorOpenPath

A boolean value when set true will force an interior open path to be milled centerline.  If false additional moves will be added above material to set comp prior to the cut.

LinkedOutlines

Link part outlines on a nest as one continuous operations

Allow6thFace

Allow 6th face output on a nest.  The 6th face pattern would be milled first, then the sheet would be flipped and the rest of the sheet would be milled

CommonLineCutting

Set part spacing to outline tool diameter and allow for a common cut between two parts

CommonLineMaxRetrace

Set the maximum distance a common line path can retrace over an already cut path.  A larger value will reduce the number of rapids in the outline paths

CommonLineRetraceBySmallParts

 

A boolean value set true to allow retracing around small parts.  Setting to false will increase the number of rapid moves in the output but will reduce the chance of nicking a small part that has moved

OptDrillSelection

Optimize drill sequence to minimize the number of spindle configuration changes instead of the shortest path between holes

Rotate6thFaceTrim

Rotate the position of the 6th face trip cuts to accomidate posts that modifiy the machine point of origin. 0=No Rotation, 1=90, 2=180, 3=270

SlopeArcLeadOnSpiralPocket

A boolean value set true to change the lead type on a spiral pocket from a straight plunge to a sloping arc

LinkOutlineOverlapAdj

A positive value creates additional overlap on the bridge of the linked outlines.

NoLeads

 

A boolean value when set true will output plunge lead-in/outs for all operations as well as forcing any tool comp to G41/G42 Tool Center.  This is for posts being used to create output for 3rd party vendors that only want geometry.

WorkplaneAxisYHoriz

A boolean value when set true to set the local Y axis on a work plane horizontal (parallel to the default work plane).  If false, the X axis will be horizontal (parallel to the default work plane).

WorkplaneAxisCWTilt

A boolean value when set true to make the axis change move in a clockwise direction as opposed to the default counter-clockwise direction.

MixHoleDiameters

A boolean value when set true will allow for a single multi-drill drop to mill holes of mixed diameters.

LastUpdate

Time stamp on when this record was last modified

0x200=Drill To Shoulder

0x400=Spindle Speed

0x800=Height Offset ID

0x1000=A/B/C-Axis Rotation

ShowXProps

 

 

A flag to show extended Machine Properties for this Link:

0x01 = Extended DXF Properties

0x02 = AlphaCAM Properties

ShowXEdgeProps

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

A flag to show extended Edge Properties for this link:

0x01 = Show Horizontal Match Drill

0x02 = Show Horizontal Match Dowel

0x04 = Show Horizontal Match KD

0x08 = Show Horizontal Match Glue

0x10 = Show Horizontal Glue Duration Milliseconds

0x20 = Show Zone 1-4

0x40 = Show Zone 4-1

ShowXMatHandlerProps

 

 

 

 

Flags to show material handler properties for this link:

0x01=ImportFile

0x02=AutoSyncOnOptimize

0x04=OffcutImportFile

0x08=AutoMakeImportFileCmd

Unique record identifier

MachineOverride

This table stores any overrides placed on Materials.

Field

Description

ID

Unique Primary Reference

MachineSetID

A cross reference to [Machine].[ID] linking this record to a MachineSet

MaterialID

A cross reference to [Material].[ID] linking this record to a material

TrimTop

Value representing the Top Trim override.

TrimFront

Value representing the Front Trim override.

TrimBack

Value representing the Back Trim override.

TrimBottom

Value representing the Bottom Trim override.

FirstCut

 

 

 

Value specifying the First Cut Type:

0 = Rip Cut

1 = Head (Cross) Cut

2 = Either

Priority

 

 

Value specifying the Optimization priority:

0 = Yield

1 = Labor

StripSort

 

 

Value specifying the Strip sort preference:

0 = Ascend

1 = Descend

Quality

 

 

 

 

A value representing the selected Optimization Quality:

1 = Fast

2 = Good

3 = Better

4 = Best

MinStripWidth

A value representing the Minimum allowable Strip Width within a Pattern.

MaxStripWidth

A value representing the Maximum allowable Strip Width within a Pattern.

MinStripLength

A value representing the Minimum allowable Strip Length within a Pattern.

MaxStripLength

A value representing the Maximum allowable Strip Length within a Pattern.

PartSort

 

 

Value specifying the Part sort preference:

0 = Ascend

1 = Descend

StepAngle

A value representing the Angle increment for Geometric (TrueShape) Nesting.

GeometricNest

A Boolean value set to true if Nesting is set to use Geometric (TrueShape) Nesting.

OffcutWidth

A value representing the Minimum Width to be considered an Offcut rather than scrap.

OffcutLength

A value representing the Minimum Length to be considered an Offcut rather than scrap.

MinTCutWidth

A value representing the Minimum Part Width that can be created with a T-Cut.

MaxTCutLength

A value representing the Maximum Part Length that can be created with a T-Cut.

SquareOffNest

A Boolean value set to true if the system is set to Square-Off the Nest to produce rectangular Offcuts.

CommonLineCutting

Set part spacing to outline tool diameter and allow for a common cut between two parts

CommonLineMaxRetrace

Set the maximum distance a common line path can retrace over an already cut path.  A larger value will reduce the number of rapids in the outline paths

CommonLineRetraceBySmallParts

 

A boolean value set true to allow retracing around small parts.  Setting to false will increase the number of rapid moves in the output but will reduce the chance of nicking a small part that has moved

PackVertical

Determines if the nest pack will prefer a vertical or horizontal pack

PackForceDir

Pack direction on a block nest is not forced, it could pack the opposite direction if it means a larger offcut. This option will force the direction set by PackVertical

SheetPriority

Specifies the order where different sheet sizes are used; 0=Price (low to high), 1=Size (small to large) 2=Yield (best fit)

SmallBoundary

Restricts small part placement on a true shape nest to inside this boundary from the sheet edge

VerySmallBoundary

Restricts very small part placement on a true shape nest to inside this boundary from the sheet edge

NoZCuts

Eliminate Z-Cuts in patterns. Z-Cuts are the 3rd phase cut in a strip

NoTCuts

Eliminate T-Cuts in patterns. T-Cuts are multiple equal 3rd phase cuts in a strip that can define the strip width.

VerySmallBoundaryShape

 

 

A value representing the Very Small Part Boundaries Shape:

0 = Exterior

1 = Interior Cross

SmallBoundaryShape

 

 

 

 

0 = Exterior
2 = Bottom Left Corner
3 = Top Left Corner
4 = Top Right Corner
5 = Bottom Right Corner

OffcutsFirst

 

The default is for the offcuts and waste to occur at the end of the sheet, strip, etc. WithB this option set the offcut and waste will be cut first.  Note: Grain Matching takes priority over this opiton.

OffcutDiscount

Valid range of 0 - 100 representing a percentage discount on offcuts - a higher value will favor offcuts as sheets instaed of full sheets

ReduceBins

Valid range of 0 - 5 as the value increases the less likely offcuts will be used from different bins.

OffcutSizePriority

0) No preference, 1) Prefer smaller offcuts, 2) Prefer larger offcuts

NoOffcutsFromOffcut

A boolean value when set true will limit offcut selection to offcuts that do not produce new offcuts.

SheetSideUp

 

 

 

Saw sheet side up preference
0 = Finished Side Up
1 = Finished Side Down
2 = Most operations up

OffcutTrimFront

Amount to trim off front side of offcut sheet

OffcutTrimBack

Amount to trim off back side of offcut sheet

OffcutTrimTop

Amount to trim off top side of offcut sheet

OffcutTrimBottom

Amount to trim off bottom side of offcut sheet

LastUpdate

Time stamp on when this record was last modified

Tool

This table stores all the Tools.

Field

Description

ID

A unique number to reference this Tool.

Name

The Tool name.

ToolTypeID

 

Size

A value representing the Tool size (Saw Kerf, or Router or Drill Bit Diameters.

WorkDepth

A value representing the allowable working depth for the Tool.

Kerf

The cutting width of a 5-axis saw blade

ToolNumber

Number for the tool specified on the machine

MachineID

Reference to [Machines.ID].linking the tool to a machine. 0=Any Machine, -1=Unavailable, -2=Multiple Machines (ToolAssignments)

OneQtrFeedRate

 

A value representing the user-defined feed rate for 1/4-inch deep cut. Used to dynamically output varying feed rates based on depth of cut and percentage value entered into Material Catalog.

ThreeQtrFeedRate

 

A value representing the user-defined feed rate for 3/4-inch deep cut. Used to dynamically output varying feed rates based on depth of cut and percentage value entered into Material Catalog.

DescentRate

A value representing the Descent rate for the Tool.

SpindleSpeed

Tool rotation speed

RotateCW

A Boolean value set to true if the Tool rotation is Clockwise.

Direction

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

A value representing the allowable Tool movement direction:

0x00 = Any

0x01 = Positive X

0x02 = Negative X

0x03 = Either X

0x04 = Positive Y

0x08 = Negative Y

0x12 = Either Y

0x15 = Either X or Y

Through

A Boolean value set to true if this Tool is the Preferred tool to use when an Operation goes through Material.

CleanFace

A Boolean value set to true if the Tool creates a clean face for the Part. (Down Shear)

CleanBack

A Boolean value set to true if the Tool creates a clean back face for the Part (Up Shear).

MaxDepthPerPass

A value representing the Maximum depth the Tool can move through a Material per pass.

OutlineTool

A Boolean value set to true if this Tool can to be used for cutting the Outline of a Part.

AutoSelect

A boolean value set true if the tool is availalbe for auto selection.  Only applies to flat router bits and drills.

SelectTolerance

Allowable variance between tool and hole diameter for tool selection

Profile

 

 

 

 

 

 

The Tools Shape in an ASCII comma delimited string.

Format:(node count,x1,x2 ,radius1,flags1,.....xN,yN, radiusN,flagsN)

 

Flags:

0x08=VTX_Radius

0x0400=VTX_ArcLine

0x010000=VTX_Visible

OuputCenterLine

A Boolean value set to true if this Tool is Output with a Center Line path vs. a Compensated Path.

ThroughDepthAdj

A value representing the additional depth to be added to operations going completely through the Material.

DrillConeAngle

A value representing the Angle of Drill Bit Tip (cone).

DrillToShoulder

A value instructing the System to Extend the Drill Depths by the Drill Cone Height.

HeightOffsetRegister

A value representing the location of the Height Offset Register on the Machine Control for this Tool.

Lollipop

A Boolean value set to true if the Ball or Bull-Nose Router bit has a Lollipop shape.

ShankDiam

A value representing the Tool shank Diameter for a Lollipop Tool.

CornerRadius

A value representing the Bull-Nose Router Bit Corner Radius.

SideWall

Vertical side wall above the shape of the tool (currently only used for V-Bit)

NestGapPad

Additional padding beyond the cut width when nesting (currently only used for V-Bit)

ABAxisRot

A Boolean value set to true if tool rotation +/- value in the A or B axis is allowed.

CAxisRot

A Boolean value set to true if tool rotation +/- value in the C axis is allowed.

TopRadius

Top radius for dovetail tool

YPosAtMin

Y Position at the smallest part of the dovetail tool

MinWidth

Smallest part of the dovetail tool

MaxWidth

Largest part of the dovetail tool

Pen

A value representing the CAD pen.

Layer

The CAD layer name.

rGUID

A global unique reference for this tool

ContributorID

A cross reference to [Contributor].[ID] indicating the source of this item

LastUpdate

Tracks last update for the record for Network and offline conflict resolution.

Field

Description

ID

Unique Primary Reference

CutForGlass

A Boolean value set to true if the Tool Set can be used for Cut for Glass MDF Doors.

ShapedGlass

A Boolean value set to true if the Tool Set path follows each glass shape as opposed to one rectangular glass panel for all lites.

RabbetWidth

A value representing the Width of rabbet to create on the back of the MDF Door for glass insertion.

RabbetDepth

A value representing the Depth of rabbet to create on the back of the MDF Door for glass insertion.

Cross-reference to [Tools].[ID] linking the Tool to use for the Back Pocket for MDF glass doors.

A value representing the additional margin added to the existing nest margin to provide clearance when the Tool Set is used for an Outline cut.

DoorOutsideEdge

A Boolean value set to true if the Tool Set can be used for a door outside edge profile.

DoorInsideEdge

A Boolean value set to true if the Tool Set can be used for a door inside edge profile.

DoorRaisedPanel

A Boolean value set to true if the Tool Set can be used for a door raised panel detail.

DoorRoute

A Boolean value set to true if the Tool Set can be used for a door route path.

FemalePlungeDepth

Depth the dovetail tool plunges into the material thickness of the female part

FemaleCutDepth

Distance the dovetail tool travels into the female part

FemaleCutAdj

Adjustment to widen female cut

FemalePocketToolID

Reference to [Tools.ID] linking the tool used to create the pocket for the dovetail plunge

FemalePocketWidth

Width of pocket created for dovetail plunge.  This value must exceed dovetail MaxWidth

FemalePocketDepth

Depth of pocket created for dovetail plunge

MaleRabbetToolID

Reference to [Tools.ID] linking the tool used to create the rabbet for the male part

MaleRabbetDepth

Depth of rabbet on male part

MaleOutlineToolID

Reference to [Tools.ID] linking the tool used to create the outline for the male part.  Tool radius must be less then tool's TopRadius value

TailExtension

Unlike the FemaleCutAdj this value effect both male and female paths effectively widening the dovetail.

ToolSetMap

This table stores the extra Tool information for the Tools assigned in a Tool Set.

Field

Description

ID

A unique number to reference this Tool Set.

MasterToolID

Cross-reference to [Tools].[ID] indicating what Tool Set this record is associated with.

Ordinal

A value representing the Order of the Tool within the Tool Set.

SlaveToolID

Cross-reference to [Tools].[ID] linking a Tool that is used in this Tool Set.

Offset

A value representing the Offset from Tool Center to Route Path.

Depth

A value representing the Depth of this operation

DropOffset

A value representing the Additional offset used for clearance when tool profile prohibits a direct plunge into material

CutForGlass

This is the tool used for front side cut for glass operation.  The depth will dynamically set to material thickness minus 1/2 rabbet depth

ToolsetOpTypeID

Reference to [refToolsetOperationType].[ID] indicating the type of operation: 1=Rough/Finish, 2=Engrave, 3=Pocket, 4=Clean Up (Inside), 5=Vertical Slats, 6=Horizontal Slats, 7=Finish (Clean Up Outside), 8=Clean Up Profile

CleanSideRight

Determines clockwise vs. counter clockwise path based on tool rotation and material climb cut.  Set true to favor the right side, false to favor the left

StartAtCorner

Route path will start at corner of part (engrave only)

DepthReference

0=Top of Part, 1=Bottom of Part, 2=Operation Depth

CleanUpRadius

A value representing the Radius of tool to clean up after.  Use a small tool and create a pocket operation for cleaner corners

SlatEdgeGap

A value representing the Gap between route path and start/end of slats.

FixedSlatWidth

A boolean value set true if the slats are a fixed width with the extra divided between the first and last.  If set false all slat widths are equalized.

MaxError

This value is used to calculate the depths of cut and determines the surface finish. The depth of cut is calculated by moving the tool out by the Maximum Error then down till the contact point meets the slope.

MaxDepthPerCut

This is the depth of cut used if the depth calculated by the Maximum Error exceeds this value.

CleanBothSides

Clean up corners on the opposite side of the original tool path.

LastUpdate

Time stamp on when this record was last modified

Unique record identifier

Description

A cross reference to [refUCSObjectType].[ID] indicating a PartID=1, IJointID=2, Dovetail ToolID=3, Door=4, DrwFrnt=5, Dado=6, HBore=7, VBore=8

A Part, Tool or IJoint GUID based on the UCSObjectTypeID

LinkToGUID

A cross reference to the [CxMaterials].[Part].[rGUID] of the part this object is linked to

AssemblyName

Represents the assembly Name chosen for the UCS. Wildcards * and ? are allowed.

PartMaterialID

Represents the Material selected for the Part in the UCS. Cross referenced to [Material].[ID]

PartDisplay

A boolean flag set true if the Part is to be displayed graphically.

LibraryPart

The location of the Library Part called in the UCS.

Code

The actual coding that makes up the UCS.

CodeModified

A boolean flag set true if the UCS has been manually modified.

Disabled

A boolean flag set true if the UCS has been disabled.

PreBuild

A boolean flag set true if the UCS should be applied prior to build.
